result.execSummary:
The defendant James Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant James Anderson in court with attorney Mark Allan Dluzak.  Alicia H. Korte appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.  

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  THE COURT ORDERED THE  Defendant to serve 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction (HOC), to run concurrent as to each count with credit for 3 days time served.  Huber privileges pursuant to Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats to apply for work and treatment.

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS, as to each count, with the following conditions:
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  Pay the DNA fee only, out of bail on deposit, if any; with the balance due during the period of the probationary period. Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  The Court waives all other costs and surcharges. Defendant indigent,
*  Maintain full time / part time employment and or schooling.
*  AODA assessment with follow up care and treatment.
*  Restitution in the amount of $370.00 to the victim James C. to be paid through the agent.
*  No contact with the victims James C. and Roger R.

Received and filed with the court:
*  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief Form
*  Restitution Work Sheet
*  Crime Victim Impact Statement
